Skara-krets, led. av styr. f. Skara komm. flicksk. o. styr. f. Skara stads sk. f. yrkesunderv., stud :cirkelkdare i ABF, föreläsare. Res. t. Danm., Finl., Tyskl., Schweiz. *Åsland, Harald Bertram, disponent, Strömstad, f. 10/5/07 i Stavanger, Norge, av disp. H. A. A. o. Bertha Fuggelli. G. m. Anna Goksör. — Real-sk. Anst. i konservind. ’sed. 22. Verkst. dir. o. styr :led. i Strömstad Canning Co., grund. 30, disp. o. istyr :led. i A-B Gbgs konservfabr. Hobbies: jakt, fiske.
translated:
Åsbrink, Eva Margareta Theodora, high school teacher. Skara, born on September 30, 1912 in Helsinki, daughter of pastor Ernst A. and Gundel Herlitz. Obtained secondary school diploma in Gävle in 1931, theological philosophy degree in Uppsala in 1933, theology candidate degree in 1937, philosophy candidate degree in 1938. Completed probationary year at Hvitfeldtska high school in Gothenburg in 1943. Part-time teacher in Eksjö from 1939-1940, at Hälsingborg boys' school in 1940, full-time teacher since 1941, assistant teacher in Skara from 1941-1943 and 1944, teacher of Christianity and Swedish language since 1944. Chairperson of the Fredrika Bremer Association and county association in Skaraborg, chairperson of the Fredrika Bremer Association's Skara district, member of the boards for Skara municipal girls' school and Skara city vocational school, study circle leader for the Workers' Educational Association (ABF), lecturer. Traveled to Denmark, Finland, Germany, Switzerland.

*Åsland, Harald Bertram, manager, Strömstad, born on May 10, 1907 in Stavanger, Norway, son of manager H. A. A. and Bertha Fuggelli. Married to Anna Goksör. Attended real school and trained in the canning industry since 1922. Executive director and board member of Strömstad Canning Company, founded in 1930, manager and board member of AB Gothenburg Canning Factory. Hobbies include hunting and fishing.
